rComments: Honestly. Larry is such a sweetheart. You need to go to lectures to do well on the exams. His assignments are pretty easy and straightforward.

HANDS DOWN one of the best profs I've had in all of my undergrad. not only is he extremely easy, (all the exam is lecture based) he is genuinely caring and wants everyone to do well and constantly gives out bonus marks. he wastes a lot of time goofing off but its so worth it because he's so kind. I'd be weary of the assignment the TA marks it

Larry is the most caring prof I've ever met. He makes sure you understand the material before moving on and always tries to find a way to relieve stress off students' backs. Attending lectures is a MUST because there are no set weekly slides; he just lectures from random slides that can sometimes take weeks to finish or half an hour. Overall, easy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Respected']

rComments: While I think Larry is funny, know's what he knows, and caring to students, I think he has a lot to improve on. He was the one who said, "It's not easy teaching," and he isn't wrong on that one. His teaching style is misguided in terms of what we need to learn and what he presents to us, as he is constantly seeking validation from us to like him.
very chill prof. he jokes a lot. motivating prof makes u want to learn

Prof. Sawchuck is an excellent lecturer. To do well on the midterm its important to actually do the assigned readings. The first few assignments are marked on completion and the final assignment can be a little challenging so make sure you get extra help on that. The final exam was fair. Sawchuck covered some of the assigned readings in lecture.
Very entertaining prof, and cracks the funniest jokes! His exams are hard and you really need to know the material. Assignments are straight forward and not bad.

rComments: He's very funny and nice. However, I found most of his lecture quality to be lacking as he always tended to get off subject. Lianne on the other hand was not very accommodating when it came to extra help and she's a pretty tough marker.

OK lets be clear this is NOT an anthropology course! this is a GENETICS course! All you will be learning is diseases and how to do punnet squares based on disease. His exams are not a cake walk! He will ask you very small details from every slide. You will read 13 really dense articles that you need to know everything for exam!
This man is the sweetest, kindest man on the planet! Great professor, well versed in the subject he teaches, and absolutely adorable! I love you to the moon and back Prof. Sawchuk.

absolutely amazing. lots of opportunities for bonus marks. if you go to each lecture there no way you can do bad in this class. make sure he knows who you are

rComments: Prof. Sawchuck is the nicest professor on all of U of T and I am confident saying that even though I haven't met most of the others. His quirky jokes are entertaining and sometimes a little dark, but amusing nonetheless! I am honoured to have taken four classes with him :)
